This paper deals with personalized recommendation problems, which are typically addressed in the machine learning and artificial intelligence communities. The use of Bayesian treatment and matrix factorization methods further suggests that this paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), social and information networks (cs.SI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
